GO Exercise Collection
(Implemented during rihal intern period)

Brief
-----
This repository is a small collection of CLI exercises written in Go. It's meant as a hands-on learning playground to get comfortable with basic Go features: packages, functions, slices/arrays, maps, structs, and standard input/output.

What this does
--------------
- Provides three difficulty tiers: `easy`, `medium`, and `hard`.
- Each tier exposes a menu-driven CLI you can run from `main.go`.
- Exercises are intentionally small and focus on core language constructs and basic algorithms (sorting, searching, string handling, simple data structures).

How to run
----------
1. Install Go (1.18+ recommended).
2. From the repository root run "go run main.go"

This starts the CLI. Choose a difficulty and follow prompts. Each exercise will ask for input and print results.

Directory layout (important files)

- `main.go` — entry point and main menu selector.
- `easy/` — beginner exercises and `Easy(reader *bufio.Reader)` menu.
- `medium/` — intermediate exercises and `Medium(reader *bufio.Reader)` menu.
- `hard/` — advanced exercises split into submodules (arrays, strings, maps, structs).
- `go.mod` — module file.

Small dictionary (terms used in the CLI)
--------------------------------------
- getInput: helper function that prompts the user and returns trimmed input from stdin.
- Input* functions: small wrappers that read and validate specific inputs (mirrors style from `easy`/`medium`).
- Hard/Medium/Easy: package-level functions that accept a `*bufio.Reader` and run a menu loop.
- Press Enter to continue: after an exercise finishes, you will usually press Enter to return to the submenu.

Notes and next steps
--------------------
- The project is intentionally minimal and educational so you can do it by your self also.

Enjoy learning Go!
